Tony Gemignani is the owner of Toscano Brother's Bakery in North Beach, San Francisco. Along with being a world-renowned Pizza Champion, he is also the lead at the International School of Pizza where he teaches all the ins and outs on how to run a successful business. Our own Evan Inada has helped him teach the antipasti/salumi course for classes and has always admired his passion and ownership of his craft. 🥖

#charcuterie #charcuterieboard #craftmeats #salumi #bakery #sanfrancisco

SF Brewing Company is owned by Josh Leavy who comes from a bloodline of brewers dating back centuries. His passion for his craft in creating new and exciting beer flavors influenced by the San Francisco Bay Area resonates with our Charcuterie Director, Evan Inada, and our passion for making salami at Columbus. Great artistry and salesmanship unite to create a great brand, which is located in the heart of Ghirardelli Square in downtown San Francisco. 🍺

latestIgtvVideos.title: Perfect Charcuterie Bite Bold & Bleu
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Say Hello to Bold & Bleu. 🤩

Pear, pecan, chocolate and caramel in Bold & Bleu make for a luscious play of sweet, creamy and salty notes. Our peppery Calabrese Salami triggers a subtle heat that pairs beautifully with the creaminess of the bleu cheese. It’s a big flavor experience, filled with potent tastes and textures, all brought into satisfying harmony by the expert hand of our charcuterie director, Evan Inada. Bold & Bleu: it’s our wake-up call for taste buds everywhere.

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Accent your board with accoutrements that provide extra elements of flavor to build off the perfect combinations you create. We'll guide you through the six essential elements to take into consideration. Each plays an important role in creating the ideal flavor profile to give you all the best results. Get ready to dig in. 🥳

latestIgtvVideos.title: Acid & Crunch in Charcuterie Boards
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Our latest live event hosted by Evan Inada, our charcuterie director, builds off why to start with salami and cheese as the basis of your charcuterie board and moves to how to best add accoutrements. Evan shares his expertise for using "acid" and "crunch" elements to elevate charcuterie pairings. Watch the video to learn how to make pickled vegetables, olives, fresh fruit, nuts, chocolate and more work for your board.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Intro to Charcuterie
latestIgtvVideos.caption: We kick off a series of live social media events hosted by Evan Inada, our charcuterie director, beginning with why salami should serve as the basis of your charcuterie board. Evan shares the depth of salami flavors available within our brand line, as well as pairing suggestions. Watch the video to hear about "the art and science" behind salami favorites, ranging from mild to spicy.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Charcuterie 101
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
To create an inspiring charcuterie board, set the tone by starting with salumi. This video will walk you through everything you need to know about mild salami, rustic salami and spicy salami.
When COLUMBUS® Craft Meats serve as the centerpiece, you’ll have a board that balances quality taste with the most appetizing accoutrements. The end result will be as special in presentation as it is in flavor. Trust us.
